 herders' adaptive strategies at a time of rapid socio-political and environmental changes in these areas of the world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aHuman-animal relationshipszMongolia. 0aHuman-animal relationshipszRussia (Federation)zBuri︠a︡tii︠a︡. 0aNomadsxSocial life and customszMongolia. 0aNomadsxSocial life and customszRussia (Federation)zBuri︠a︡tii︠a︡. 0aPastureszMongolia. 0aPastureszRussia (Federation)zBuri︠a︡tii︠a︡. 4aAnthropology. 4aAsian Studies. 4aEast Asia and North East Asia. 4aSociology and Social History. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aAnthropology, nomadism, Mongols, human-animal relations, environmental and social changes.1 aBillé, Franck.1 aHumphrey, Caroline.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311074322708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2z978311074335708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021 Englishz978311075418608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021z9783110753967oZDB-23-DSL40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048550111?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048550111423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789048550111/original  a978-3-11-074322-7  Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-074335-7  DG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075418-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021 Englishb2021  